To the situation in Afghanistan and Pakistan and to terrorism, the latter condemned in all its forms by both sides, and called for the convening of a UN conference.
They called for the conclusion of the Doha Trade Round, although both sides played a role in the failure of this.
The EU has confirmed that it remains committed to the energy and climate programme, i.e. it wants to reduce emissions of harmful substances by at least 20% by 2020.
India also agrees on this, as well as on the fact that a global pact should be reached at the climate conference scheduled for next year and reduce greenhouse gas production by 50% by 2050.
They also want to curb rising food prices and have supported convening an international meeting to discuss the financial crisis.
The Indian Prime Minister will travel to the French capital where in a bilateral meeting he is preparing to sign a treaty on the peaceful use of atomic energy.
